The paper discusses an optimization strategy using Artificial Bee Colony (ABC) algorithm, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of a local search strategy inspired by memetic algorithm, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves probabilistic approaches and population-based algorithms, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper also discusses the optimization of engineering problems, which can be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
